-Constructor
  It is called constructor because it constructs the values at the time of object creation
 -Its like a special method
 Its special because:
   name of method is same as name of class
   unlike method this will not have return type
   unlike method we don't have to call the constructors, this is called automatically the moment we create object of the class

 Constructor Overloading is possible. In order to call the overloaded constructor, we need to create
 Object and pass the value as per the constructor to be called.

 -Constructors also act as value setters of the class properties[global variables]
